|~ Catalog of named-error type-bindings вЂ” one entry per JS-side
   class declared in core/src/operand-errors.mjs and the
   special error-convert sources (ParseError, foreign-error
   names, axis-operand failures). Each declaration is the
   minimum that makes the tag known to the env so
   `evalBareTypeKeyword` finds it and authors can write
   `!{:thrown ::Tag вЂ¦}` literals or `:add | /throws | first
   | docs` axis navigations.

   Sections are grouped by the originating operand's
   `:category` (matching the catalog ordering of core.qlang)
   plus a tail of runtime-invariant sections (projection,
   combinator track-dispatch, parse, codec, dispatch, registry,
   session, print). Generated by `scripts/generate-error-registry.mjs`.

   Constructors (Quote-impl validators per В§II.3 of the
   redesign plan) land in a later pass. ~|

